            <div class="clean-post-card">
              <h2>End of Year’s Message from ACM-W India Chair<br>– Dr. Geetanjali Kale</h2>
              
              <div class="img-alignright" style="border: none; background: none;">
                 <img src="data:image/png;base64," alt="Dr. Geetanjali Kale" style="width: 100%; height: 100%; object-fit: cover; border-radius: 4px; border: 1px solid #ddd; box-shadow: 0 2px 5px rgba(0,0,0,0.1);">
              </div>
              
              <p>Welcome to the December 2025 edition of the ACM-W India Newsletter. As the year ends, let us take a moment to reflect on the journey we’ve shared this year!</p>

              <p>In 2025, the ACM-W India chapters network welcomed several new chapters across the country. A warm welcome to all new chapters, and a huge thank-you to all the chapter officers who have taken the initiative to establish them! Their efforts help create local communities in which women in computing can thrive, collaborate, and innovate.</p>
              
              <div class="img-aligncenter" style="border: none; background: none;">
                 <img src="data:image/jpeg;base64," alt="Grad Cohort 25" style="width: 100%; height: 100%; object-fit: cover; border-radius: 4px; border: 1px solid #ddd; box-shadow: 0 2px 5px rgba(0,0,0,0.1);">
              </div>
              
              <p>2025 was also a year of fantastic events that inspired women in computing from all around the country. Our flagship events, <strong>Lady Ada</strong>, <strong>Nariyukti</strong>, and <strong>Grad Cohort</strong>, brought together hundreds of attendees to learn from one another, network, and celebrate the achievements of women in computing.</p>
              
              <p>As we look ahead to 2026, we would like to extend our sincere thanks to all members of our community who have contributed to our work over the past year. In particular, we are grateful to the ACM-W India Executive Committee; the organizing committees of our flagship events; our chapter officers; and all our volunteers. The achievements of ACM-W India are possible only through your commitment and hard work.</p>
              
              <p>Whatever the coming year may hold, we look forward to supporting you and to celebrating your professional and personal milestones.</p>
              
              <p>Happy new year!<br><strong>Dr. Geetanjali Kale</strong><br>ACM-W India Chair</p>
              
